		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/privatemsg.gif" border="0" alt="Click Here to Message Nosferatu" width="22" height="11"></a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
		
		<a href="MB_editmsg.asp?FID=68&FN=Ranger&SID=7&SN=EverQuest&TID=1988838&TN=Aggro+Management&CAT=Classes&SURL=http%3A%2F%2Fwww%2Eeverlore%2Ecom&MSID=1989105&PL=4">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/edit.gif" border="0" alt="Edit/Delete Message" width="18" height="13"></a>
		
		</font>
		<hr size="1">No offense to rangers, but they are nowhere near the best aggro managers.  Matter of fact, of any class, they have to be very aware of their aggro - and at lower levels, in groups, can have problems doing so w/o jolt.</P><P>If you are in a group, and you have too much aggro...stop attacking.  It's that simple.  Whomever is playing MA should be able to get the aggro back very quickly.</P><P>That doesn't mean that Rangers can't be MA...I've played alongside many Rangers that are very good at doing so.  But it depends on the circumstances.<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
	</font>
