		<hr size="1">Feign Death, and its later version, Death Peace, are not what I would call "aggro management".  Its an all or nothing ability that doesn't allow for incremental adjustments like the Ranger spells.  Either the spell works and you drop completely off the list, or it doesnt and you get beat on for the next 15 seconds (FD) or 6 seconds (Death Peace).  Thats like saying Power Management for an electrical company is either turning the entire City on or off.  You can't really use it to ride the aggro line behind the MT and be in a place to take over immediately should the MT die.</P><P>But, since you brought up instant aggro drop, you left off Paladins and their ability to DA, which is superior, in pure terms of switching the NPC to another target, than Feign Death.  The issues with DA though are that it has a long recast, lasts 18 seconds and the paladin has to hope that someone managed to get more aggro than he had before the DA, or he gets hit again when it fades, and during those 18 seconds, he can't get healed to drop blood lust aggro.  Unlike FD though, DA doesn't erase the Paladins aggro points, so he is right where he was, and hopefully by this time right behind the MT.</P><P>Like I said though, if you want actually manage your aggro to keep you high on the list, ie above the casters and below the MT, a Ranger has the best set of tools.<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
	</font>
