		<hr size="1">Rely on a druid to drop in and make comments like that. Two things Nahallic, one is rangers can tank and given the situation make better tanks than the classes you mentioned, for the main reason that we can get agro and hold agro (if needed, and I have been the MA for many EXP groups) and two just because a ranger gets agro does not me they are using taunt (I don't even keep a taunt key up unless I am the MA for a group).</P><P>The best teacher for agro management is practice. Test out the recommendations listed above and see what works for you.<BR>I dispise turning auto attack off and doing nothing at all, if I am forced to stop attack, I always make use of that time, usually casting spells. If you are near the top of hte agro list, try casting a self buff, most of our self buffs are faily long casts, and that can be enough time to let the MA build agro, try two or three smaller ones for similar results.</P><P>Healing can build agro, but our heals are small enough and slow enough that it won't be a problem, so you can also try tossing a couple heals in the down time, instead of auto off and waiting.</P><P>Another option is to back away from the fight nad use your bow for a bit. If you are low enough that you cannot cast jolt, then you aren't going to gink agro off the tank with your bow. After half a dozen arrows, try going back into melee range and continue from there.</P><P>Gorse Shadowwood<BR>Level 62 Warder<BR>202 Skill Level Fletcher<BR>Tunare server<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
